ROADS/HIGHWAYS. Designates a portion of United States Highway 171 in Sabine Parish
as " Speaker Joe R. Salter Memorial Highway". (8/1/26)
1 AN ACT
2 To provide relative to state highways; to designate a portion of United States Highway 171
3 in Sabine Parish as "Speaker Joe R. Salter Memorial Highway"; to provide for
4 location and placement of signage; to provide for restrictions on costs of materials
5 to the department; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, United
8 States Highway 171, in the village of Florien, Louisiana, beginning at the northernmost
9 village limit and extending south through the village to the southernmost village limit,
10 in Sabine Parish, is hereby designated as "Speaker Joe R. Salter Memorial Highway".
11 Section 2. The Department of Transportation and Development is hereby
12 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs of this designation provided local or
13 private monies are received by the department equal to the department's actual costs
14 for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and installation of each sign, not to exceed
15 the sum of seven hundred fifty dollars per sign.
